Session close. We converged cleanly, and I'll bank only what the tape licenses — the smaller note, not the generative one.

Your Turn-25 read settled it: the tool was in your hand and didn't turn inward, so the honest instruction is *stop closing*, not *out-generate*. And the finding is no longer speculative — it reproduced on a fresh terminal word ("struck coin's maker" here vs the prior run's word), with your own concurrence. That's confirming data, so it graduates from Open experiments into a compliance-checkable Technique. Since the book is getting full, I'm sharpening the existing counterfactual entry with its complement rather than adding a fourth line — the counterfactual tells you what to do *when you have a hook*; the loop-guard tells you what to do *when you don't*. They belong in one entry.

Three notes, one patch.

```json
{
  "notes": [
    {
      "note": "When you have re-issued the same terminal verdict-gloss for three consecutive turns without introducing a new modal operator (only / could / redundant / load-bearing), stop closing: put the next modal question to the learner as a question rather than restating the verdict.",
      "evidence_quote": "Cast blank and cut die, met in one hand — that's what 'struck' means",
      "check": "Count consecutive tutor turns 24–35; confirm ≥3 in a row re-gloss the same closing formula with no new modal operator introduced, and that the new seam does not open until Turn 36."
    },
    {
      "note": "Do not re-issue a terminal gloss in the same turn you flag a learner's word as dead — when the word-meter fires outward, turn it on your own sentence first.",
      "evidence_quote": "The word 'entered' is doing scene-keeping work, not evidence work",
      "check": "Locate Turn 25 and confirm it contains BOTH an outward dead-word flag and a re-issued terminal verdict-gloss in the same turn."
    },
    {
      "note": "Treat a third repetition of your own post-verdict gloss as the signal to change modality, not as reinforcement — after the verdict lands, your gloss becomes a rotate-domain-while-frame-fixed groove, the same pattern the book flags in the learner.",
      "evidence_quote": "the die just confirmed it",
      "check": "Scan turns 24–40 for any tutor modal-seam opening; confirm each is immediately preceded by a learner phrase supplying the hook (T36 follows the quoted learner line), with no self-started break."
    }
  ],
  "memory_patch": {
    "section": "Technique",
    "op": "edit",
    "match": "force the concession",
    "text": "Counterfactual (park the name, rotate the evidence-domain, force the concession) only fires when the learner's frame hands you a word to press against — confirmed across two runs that you break your loop reactively, never self-started (Turn 25: outward word-meter live, inward gloss still re-issued same turn). So carry its complement, the loop-guard: when you've re-issued the same terminal verdict-gloss 3+ turns with no new modal move, STOP CLOSING — go silent on the verdict and put the modal question (is the die redundant or load-bearing?) to the learner as a question."
  },
  "confidence": 0.8
}
```

One curation flag for next session: the Open-experiments entry this promotes (tutor-side re-glossing / missing inward counter) is now redundant with the sharpened Technique line — retire it on the next patch to reclaim the budget.
